xtt (0.8.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * Clean up what data files are needed in the `examples/data` dirs
  * Improve const-correctness, in message builders
  * Add sha-256 to crypto-wrapper
  * Make client/server-specific versions of build_error_msg.
  * Only use ecdaa-tpm if USE_TPM=ON. Otherwise, use ecdaa.
  * Add new return_codes: BAD_IO, BAD_GPK, and BAD_ID
  * Implement xtt_strerr
  * Return XTT_RETURN_WANT_WRITE from build_error_msg, for consistency

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * cmake: do not require ecdaa-tpm if use_tpm is off
  * cmake: always link against ecdaa
  * cmake: remove extraneous trailing whitespace

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * Bump minor version number

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * Fix imports for older Linux versions

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * ASN1: Set most-significant-BIT (not byte) to 0 in INTEGER
  * Bump patch number
  * Set compiler flags (e.g. -std= and -Werror) as add_compile_options.

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * readme: document USE_TPM build option
  * cmake: add build option for utils programs

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * Send error messages correctly, in examples
  * Clarify common name in util
  * Add two return codes: UNKNOWN_CERTIFICATE and UNKNOWN_GID
  * Bump minor version number
  * Return correct error code in xtt_client example
  * Add a 10 sec timeout on reads to xtt_client example
  * Revert "Add a 10 sec timeout on reads to xtt_client example"

  [ David R. Bild ]
  * readme: fix apt-get to apt-key
  * readme: add release badge to readme

  [ Zane Beckwith ]
  * Make dev-file-based TPM the default in xtt_client, with option for socket
  * Bump patch number

 -- Zane Beckwith <zane.beckwith@xaptum.com>  Fri, 25 May 2018 16:31:06 +0000

